turns.utterance: I'm a female so have never been in the boy scouts. My brother was a scout though. It seems like a worthwhile organization.
turns.response: I think it is! It's also one of the largest scouting organizations in the United States

turns.utterance: That's really interesting. Any idea when it was formed?
turns.response: i think it was founded in 1910 and since then more than 110 million americans have been participants

turns.utterance: That's a lot of people! What sort of activities does the organization have?
turns.response: they participate in a wide range of outdoor activities and educational programs as well

turns.utterance: That's great! Young people must get so much benefit from being members of such an organization.
turns.response: they do! and it's so good for their character development

turns.utterance: It's so important for young people to have diverse interest and develop a wide range of skills, don't you think?
turns.response: i agree with you on that! I would want my son to be in boy scouts
